16:09.801 --> 16:12.538
- Greg, Greg, are you okay?

16:14.538 --> 16:16.541
Greg, are you okay?

16:16.541 --> 16:19.043
(siren wailing)

16:19.043 --> 16:21.552
(sobbing)

16:27.552 --> 16:30.432
- [Man] Get her out of there.

16:41.432 --> 16:43.336
Careful, pull up, okay?

16:46.336 --> 16:47.639
- I really like the
songs you have planned.

16:47.639 --> 16:49.474
I've never heard
some of them before

16:49.474 --> 16:50.575
but I'm sure they're gonna be

16:50.575 --> 16:52.110
a really bit hit with everyone.

16:52.110 --> 16:53.445
- The choir's excited.

16:53.445 --> 16:55.245
Just trying to keep it fresh.

16:55.245 --> 16:57.514
Can't sing the same
songs week after week.

16:57.514 --> 16:59.517
- You'd be surprised, we've
sang the same five songs

16:59.517 --> 17:02.821
every Sunday and Wednesday
for three months straight.

17:02.821 --> 17:05.757
- That's why you hired me
as the new music minister.

17:05.757 --> 17:07.325
- Have you guys started
on that math homework yet

17:07.325 --> 17:09.661
because I'm completely lost.

17:09.661 --> 17:12.564
- I was hoping
you'd help me out.

17:12.564 --> 17:14.132
- Math is easy.

17:14.132 --> 17:16.269
I got an A on my last math test.

17:18.269 --> 17:20.137
- Okay, smart one, do you
even know what algebra is?

17:20.137 --> 17:23.473
- No, but from the sound of
it, neither do any of you.

17:23.473 --> 17:25.541
(giggling)
- She's got a point.

17:25.541 --> 17:28.482
(dramatic music)

17:31.482 --> 17:33.451
- Hey, neighbor.
- Hey.

17:33.451 --> 17:35.220
I have some horrible news.

17:35.220 --> 17:37.521
Greg and Carol, they've been
in a horrific car crash.

17:37.521 --> 17:38.823
(gasping)
- Are they okay?

17:38.823 --> 17:40.357
- Carol, she's in
serious condition

17:40.357 --> 17:42.493
but Greg, I'm afraid
he didn't make it.

17:42.493 --> 17:44.434
- Oh my God, Faith.

17:50.434 --> 17:53.907
(phone ringing)

17:56.907 --> 17:59.546
- Hey, this is Pastor Mark.

18:01.546 --> 18:02.449
What, when?

18:04.449 --> 18:05.184
Where?

18:07.184 --> 18:10.555
Oh my gosh, yeah, I'll
be there right away.

18:10.555 --> 18:13.157
Oh God, please help this family.

18:13.157 --> 18:14.659
- [Woman] What is it?

18:14.659 --> 18:16.661
- It's Greg and Carol,
there's been an accident.

18:16.661 --> 18:18.395
(dramatic music)

18:18.395 --> 18:19.696
- Alright, tell me what we got.

18:19.696 --> 18:21.532
- Female, mid-40s,
internal bleeding,

18:21.532 --> 18:24.669
BP, 85 over 60, heart
rate is weak and running.

18:24.669 --> 18:26.471
She's lost a lot of blood.

18:26.471 --> 18:27.704
We've already given her
two liters of fluid.

18:27.704 --> 18:28.673
- Gotcha, we got it from here.

18:28.673 --> 18:30.262
Let's get her to O.R. now.

18:52.262 --> 18:54.237
(lightly crying)

18:59.237 --> 19:02.472
- Hi, is there any word
on Carol Bolin yet?

19:02.472 --> 19:04.608
(light dramatic music)

19:04.608 --> 19:06.211
- No sir, she's
still in surgery.

19:06.211 --> 19:07.612
If you'd like to take a
seat at the waiting area,

19:07.612 --> 19:09.480
we'll notify you when
there's any updates on her.

19:09.480 --> 19:10.549
- Okay, thank you.

19:12.549 --> 19:15.307
(light dramatic music)

20:09.307 --> 20:11.823
(sad piano music)

20:25.823 --> 20:27.057
- Bolin Family?

21:00.057 --> 21:03.394
- Oftentimes, we feel
as though we're entitled

21:03.394 --> 21:08.098
to a certain number of days
or years on this Earth.

21:08.098 --> 21:10.968
This is part of what makes
Greg and Carol's death

21:10.968 --> 21:14.771
so much more difficult to bear.

21:14.771 --> 21:16.874
One thing I need to
remind you, though,

21:16.874 --> 21:19.076
is the Bible makes
no such promise.

21:19.076 --> 21:20.845
As a matter of fact,
the Book of James,

21:20.845 --> 21:22.946
in the fourth chapter,
tells us that our life

21:22.946 --> 21:26.817
is just a vapor that's here
today and gone tomorrow.

21:26.817 --> 21:31.855
Psalms Verse Nine and 12
teach us to number our days

21:31.855 --> 21:34.726
so that we may gain
a heart of wisdom.

21:34.726 --> 21:38.628
Death is always near us,
walking beside each of us

21:38.628 --> 21:42.400
as a constant companion and
many of you that are here today,

21:42.400 --> 21:44.402
you know that all too well.

21:44.402 --> 21:46.770
You realize that the only
reason you're still here today

21:46.770 --> 21:49.507
is because of God's
grace and mercy,

21:49.507 --> 21:50.875
where he saved you
from a situation

21:50.875 --> 21:53.411
that you shouldn't
have walked away from

21:53.411 --> 21:56.547
because it was
part of God's plan.

21:56.547 --> 22:00.050
The Bible tells us in
Matthew Chapter 29,

22:00.050 --> 22:02.720
that not one sparrow
falls from the sky

22:02.720 --> 22:05.155
without the will of God

22:05.155 --> 22:06.790
and he goes on to tell us

22:06.790 --> 22:10.728
that you are much more
valuable than many sparrows.

22:10.728 --> 22:15.633
As tragic as it is to see
the death of Greg and Carol,

22:15.633 --> 22:16.968
I wanna remind you
and comfort you

22:16.968 --> 22:20.875
that this, too, is
part of God's plan.

22:23.875 --> 22:25.942
- I don't understand.

22:25.942 --> 22:28.546
Why can't you just
come live with us?

22:28.546 --> 22:31.615
I don't want you
to leave, Faith.

22:31.615 --> 22:34.786
- [Girl] I'm gonna
miss you so much.

22:34.786 --> 22:37.688
- I know, I'm gonna
miss you both.

22:37.688 --> 22:39.824
I'll never have friends
like you ever again.

22:39.824 --> 22:41.625
- Hey, that's not true.

22:41.625 --> 22:42.027
You'll always have
friends like us

22:43.027 --> 22:45.529
because we're always
gonna be here for you.

22:45.529 --> 22:47.031
- And I mean, I know no
one can compare to us

22:48.031 --> 22:50.867
but let's face it,
you're amazing.

22:50.867 --> 22:54.910
You're gonna find amazing
people who wanna be with you.

22:58.910 --> 23:01.847
- Come here, take my hand.

23:03.847 --> 23:07.117
Dear Daddy Jesus,
thank you so much

23:07.117 --> 23:08.920
for my best friend, Faith.

23:08.920 --> 23:13.790
I love her so much and she
is such an amazing person

23:13.790 --> 23:16.827
but right now, she's going
through a really hard time

23:16.827 --> 23:18.863
and she's hurting a lot

23:18.863 --> 23:21.566
and I know all I wanna do is
have her stay here with me

23:21.566 --> 23:22.900
so I can give her a big hug

23:22.900 --> 23:25.769
and make all of her
problems go away.

23:25.769 --> 23:27.005
I know I can't do that.

23:28.005 --> 23:31.877
So God, even though it's
really hard, today I let her go

23:33.877 --> 23:36.847
so you can come and put
your arms around her

23:36.847 --> 23:38.115
'cause I know only in your arms

23:38.115 --> 23:41.519
can she truly
start to be healed.

23:41.519 --> 23:43.954
And God, I also pray that
you would bring new friends

23:43.954 --> 23:46.223
into Faith's life
that will love her

23:46.223 --> 23:49.894
and lead her down
the right path.

23:49.894 --> 23:51.895
We trust you, Jesus.

23:51.895 --> 23:53.964
You're the only reason
we can look to the future

23:53.964 --> 23:54.534
and have hope.

23:56.534 --> 24:00.045
In your mighty, loving
name we pray, Amen.

24:08.045 --> 24:09.646
(knocking on door)

24:09.646 --> 24:11.848
- Pastor Mark, can I talk
with you for a minute?

24:11.848 --> 24:13.851
- Yeah, absolutely, come on in.

24:13.851 --> 24:16.923
(light piano music)

24:18.923 --> 24:21.992
- I don't know if Faith
can cope with all of this.

24:21.992 --> 24:25.962
She just lost her parents,
has to move to a new city,

24:25.962 --> 24:27.230
leave behind all her friends

24:27.230 --> 24:30.968
and move in with family
she hardly knows.

24:30.968 --> 24:32.737
- Jay, she's gonna be alright

24:32.737 --> 24:36.540
and I know this is tough but
her name is Faith for a reason.

24:36.540 --> 24:38.075
You know, it's easy to say

24:38.075 --> 24:40.912
that God has a plan for our
life but it's times like this,

24:40.912 --> 24:44.147
we really have to have
faith and know that he does.

24:44.147 --> 24:46.284
The word reminds us that
God works all things

24:46.284 --> 24:48.219
to the good of
those that love him

24:48.219 --> 24:51.055
and are the called
according to his purposes.

24:51.055 --> 24:54.258
God really does have a
plan for Faith's life

24:54.258 --> 24:57.127
and as tough as this
may be, I promise you

24:57.127 --> 24:59.931
that God's gonna use
this to mold her life

24:59.931 --> 25:02.833
in ways that you and I
could never even imagine.

25:02.833 --> 25:04.301
- I know, but my job
is to help these kids

25:04.301 --> 25:07.637
any way that I can and I've
never experienced anything

25:07.637 --> 25:09.272
like this before.

25:09.272 --> 25:12.643
Greg and Carol
were good friends.

25:12.643 --> 25:14.979
I feel like I'm failing them.

25:14.979 --> 25:16.580
I feel like I'm failing Faith.

25:16.580 --> 25:18.249
- No Jay, you're
not failing them

25:18.249 --> 25:21.852
and you're certainly
not failing Faith.

25:21.852 --> 25:23.820
Greg and Carol were
some of the best people

25:23.820 --> 25:25.288
I've ever had the
privilege of knowing

25:25.288 --> 25:28.659
and this doesn't
just affect you.

25:28.659 --> 25:30.126
This has affected
our entire church

25:30.126 --> 25:32.663
and it's really shaken
the entire community.

25:32.663 --> 25:34.131
This loss at the
center of all of it

25:34.131 --> 25:38.035
is this innocent young
girl who's lost her parents

25:38.035 --> 25:41.905
and she's hurting, Jay, and
she just needs us right now.

25:41.905 --> 25:44.342
She needs our prayers
more than anything.

25:44.342 --> 25:48.179
She doesn't think for one
second that you're failing her.

25:48.179 --> 25:49.880
Matter of fact, just
you being here right now

25:49.880 --> 25:53.718
shows how much you really
do care about her, Jay.

25:53.718 --> 25:55.086
She's gonna be alright.

25:55.086 --> 25:57.788
God's gonna take care
of her, I promise.

25:57.788 --> 26:00.290
- I hope you're
right, Pastor Mark.

26:00.290 --> 26:02.093
- I know I am.

26:02.093 --> 26:05.032
(light dramatic music)

26:09.032 --> 26:10.836
- What do I do?

26:12.836 --> 26:15.342
How can I live without you?

26:18.342 --> 26:21.780
Why would God take
you away from me?

26:23.780 --> 26:27.121
I've always worshiped
him and praised him.

26:30.121 --> 26:31.090
What did I do wrong?

26:34.090 --> 26:36.961
Why would he do this to me?

26:37.961 --> 26:39.265
I just don't understand.

26:41.265 --> 26:43.140
(crying)

26:49.140 --> 26:52.242
- Faith, I'm sorry but we
need to get on the road.

26:52.242 --> 26:55.145
We've got a long
drive ahead of us.

26:55.145 --> 26:56.913
- I love you, Mom and Dad.

26:56.913 --> 26:59.338
I'm gonna miss you both so much.

27:55.338 --> 27:58.244
(dramatic music)

28:01.244 --> 28:04.515
- Yeah, I played golf
with the mayor yesterday.

28:04.515 --> 28:06.051
He said everything's okay.

28:08.051 --> 28:10.887
I think we got the
problem ironed down.

28:10.887 --> 28:14.290
That's right, I
had to let Ted go.

28:14.290 --> 28:17.583
He just couldn't
get the job done.

29:12.583 --> 29:14.317
I feel bad for
him and his family

29:14.317 --> 29:16.155
but, you know, it is what it is.

29:19.155 --> 29:20.565
That's right.

29:27.565 --> 29:30.267
Okay, that sounds good.

29:30.267 --> 29:31.434
We'll wrap it up tomorrow.

29:31.434 --> 29:32.148
Okay, bye.

29:45.148 --> 29:48.184
(phone ringing)

29:48.184 --> 29:49.088
Hello, this is Frank.

29:52.088 --> 29:56.494
I need you to send me the
Jacobson contracts by tomorrow.

29:58.494 --> 30:01.284
Hey, I need to call you back.

30:20.284 --> 30:23.186
(phone ringing)

30:23.186 --> 30:25.588
Hello, this is Frank.

30:25.588 --> 30:27.258
Yes, Mr. Johnson.

30:27.258 --> 30:30.294
We're gonna have everything
to you by tomorrow.

30:30.294 --> 30:31.211
That's right.

30:48.211 --> 30:50.346
- Roger, what are you doing?

30:50.346 --> 30:51.315
- What does it look
like I'm doing?

30:51.315 --> 30:53.349
I'm working on my truck.

30:53.349 --> 30:56.153
- Faith's on the way and
she's been through a lot

30:56.153 --> 30:58.288
and I want you to be
on your best behavior.

30:58.288 --> 31:00.362
- That's your family, not mine.

31:05.362 --> 31:08.246
- Here she comes,
I mean it, Roger.

31:22.246 --> 31:24.580
Hey, sweetie, you
have a good trip?

31:24.580 --> 31:25.715
- It was okay.

31:25.715 --> 31:27.317
- Okay, well come on.

31:27.317 --> 31:30.528
We'll take you up to
see your room, okay?

31:37.528 --> 31:39.166
- Hi, I'm Pastor Jay.

31:43.166 --> 31:45.337
- You can take those on inside.

31:47.337 --> 31:48.515
- Okay.

31:58.515 --> 31:59.352
Alright now, Faith.

32:01.352 --> 32:04.021
Remember, keep your namesake,
I'm only a call away.

32:05.021 --> 32:05.021
- Thank you, Pastor Jay.

32:05.756 --> 32:07.324
Thank you for everything.

32:07.324 --> 32:10.471
- You're welcome,
I'll talk to you soon.

32:21.471 --> 32:24.746
(phone ringing)

32:28.746 --> 32:29.748
- Hey.

32:30.748 --> 32:32.782
- How's it going
over there so far?

32:32.782 --> 32:34.751
- I guess okay.

32:34.751 --> 32:37.488
I don't really think
Uncle Roger wants me here.

32:37.488 --> 32:40.057
- Come on, I'm sure
that's not true.

32:40.057 --> 32:41.026
You know I miss you
so much already.

32:42.026 --> 32:43.660
I wish you could come
back and live with us.

32:43.660 --> 32:46.031
- I know, I miss you, too.

32:48.031 --> 32:50.334
I start at my new
school tomorrow.

32:50.334 --> 32:52.568
- Well, I'm sure you'll
meet plenty of new people.

32:52.568 --> 32:55.271
Just be your old happy
self and you'll be fine.

32:55.271 --> 32:58.076
- I don't know if
I can be right now.

33:00.076 --> 33:02.645
- How long is she
gonna be here anyway?

33:02.645 --> 33:04.781
- As long as she
needs to be here.

33:04.781 --> 33:07.084
We're the only
family she has left.

33:07.084 --> 33:10.054
- No, you're the only
family she has left.

33:10.054 --> 33:12.189
- Why do you keep saying that?

33:12.189 --> 33:14.691
Roger, you married
into this family.

33:14.691 --> 33:17.327
- But it's still not mine.

33:17.327 --> 33:22.165
No matter how hard you
try, it never will be.

33:22.165 --> 33:25.269
- Roger, this is our chance.

33:25.269 --> 33:29.343
This is our chance to move
forward after all these years.

33:33.343 --> 33:36.550
- [Roger] After all these years.

33:40.550 --> 33:43.246
(light peaceful music)

34:43.246 --> 34:44.481
- [Aunt] Morning, sweetie.

34:44.481 --> 34:45.449
- Morning.

34:46.449 --> 34:47.518
- [Aunt] Made you
some breakfast.

34:47.518 --> 34:49.186
Hope you like scrambled eggs.

34:49.186 --> 34:50.389
- Yes, ma'am.

34:52.389 --> 34:54.590
Lord, thank you for this food.

34:54.590 --> 34:58.599
Please bless it to the
nourishment in my body, Amen.

35:02.599 --> 35:04.204
- Just lost my appetite.

35:07.204 --> 35:09.206
Hey, hun, I'm just gonna grab
something on my way to work.

35:09.206 --> 35:10.244
- [Aunt] Okay.

35:15.244 --> 35:18.333
(light peaceful music)

36:09.333 --> 36:11.568
- Faith, hurry,
we're gonna be late.

36:11.568 --> 36:13.289
- [Faith] I'm coming.

36:32.289 --> 36:35.943
- Dogwood's pretty
this time of year.

36:53.943 --> 36:55.344
- Faith, where you going?

36:55.344 --> 36:57.947
- I'll be right back.
- Okay.

36:57.947 --> 36:59.882
(groaning)

36:59.882 --> 37:01.518
- Here, I'll get that for you.

37:01.518 --> 37:03.786
- Well, thank you, sweetie.

37:03.786 --> 37:04.822
Thank you.

37:05.822 --> 37:08.527
Oh my, you look like an angel.

37:10.527 --> 37:13.063
- Come on, Faith, we're late.

37:13.063 --> 37:15.065
- That's your name, Faith?

37:15.065 --> 37:17.668
(giggling)
- Yes, ma'am.

37:17.668 --> 37:20.871
- Don't let 'em change you.

37:20.871 --> 37:22.838
- Well, have a blessed day.

37:22.838 --> 37:26.856
- [Woman] Thank you,
you too, darling.

37:40.856 --> 37:42.759
- I'm gonna be late.

37:42.759 --> 37:45.094
Um, do you think that you
could register yourself?

37:45.094 --> 37:46.697
- [Faith] Yes, ma'am.

37:46.697 --> 37:49.432
- [Aunt] Just try
to fit in, okay?

37:49.432 --> 37:51.534
And have a good day, alright?

37:51.534 --> 37:53.750
And I'll pick you up, just go.

38:06.750 --> 38:08.452
- Watch it, freak.
- Sorry.

38:08.452 --> 38:10.722
- [Girl] You better be.

38:12.722 --> 38:15.914
(light dramatic music)

38:37.914 --> 38:41.018
- God, please keep Faith
strong in your word.

38:42.018 --> 38:44.788
I know that you are
our Father in heaven,

38:44.788 --> 38:48.157
that you can provide
for all things

38:48.157 --> 38:51.827
and that you alone are
our strongest tower,

38:51.827 --> 38:53.865
our strength and our way.

38:55.865 --> 38:58.902
Help her to face these
giants before her.

38:58.902 --> 39:00.871
Help her to understand that
even the smallest stone

39:00.871 --> 39:03.072
can vanquish the
tallest of them.

39:03.072 --> 39:06.543
My trust is given
to you, Father.

39:06.543 --> 39:07.844
Though she has lost
those who have loved

39:07.844 --> 39:11.717
and guided her thus
far, help her to endure.

39:13.717 --> 39:17.590
Let her see the way,
the only way, your way.

39:21.590 --> 39:24.563
In your son's
name, I pray, Amen.

39:27.563 --> 39:30.904
(students chattering)

39:33.904 --> 39:36.474
- Hey check it out, a new girl.

39:38.474 --> 39:39.876
They always say
modest is hottest

39:39.876 --> 39:41.911
but I think she took
that way too seriously.

39:41.911 --> 39:43.813
- Well, it's a
nice change of pace

39:43.813 --> 39:45.815
from what we usually
see around here.

39:45.815 --> 39:47.855
Come on, let's get to class.

39:51.855 --> 39:54.132
(students chattering)

40:02.132 --> 40:04.634
(bell ringing)

40:04.634 --> 40:07.538
(students chattering)

40:08.538 --> 40:09.972
- Sorry I'm late.

40:09.972 --> 40:13.951
- It's no problem, why
don't you take a seat?

40:20.951 --> 40:22.719
- I can't wait
that long, though.

40:22.719 --> 40:23.619
- Hey, Michael.

40:23.619 --> 40:24.588
- Hey, Katie.

40:25.588 --> 40:27.590
Think we're having pizza.

40:27.590 --> 40:29.925
- Hey dude, check
out her bookbag.

40:29.925 --> 40:31.862
- What is she, a nun?

40:31.862 --> 40:33.230
(chuckling)

40:33.230 --> 40:35.032
- Caleb and Jacob,
see me after class.

40:36.032 --> 40:39.936
I have some extra
homework for you two.

40:40.936 --> 40:44.608
Now class, let's give
our new classmate

40:44.608 --> 40:46.711
a proper Central High welcome.

40:48.711 --> 40:52.885
Would you stand up and tell
us a little about yourself?

40:54.885 --> 40:56.786
- My name is Faith.

40:56.786 --> 40:58.954
- [Boy] Of course it is.

40:58.954 --> 41:02.858
- I just moved to this city
to live with my aunt and uncle

41:02.858 --> 41:05.961
and that's pretty much it.

41:05.961 --> 41:07.731
- Cool story, tell it again.

41:07.731 --> 41:10.034
(giggling)

41:11.034 --> 41:13.036
- Thank you, Faith.

41:13.036 --> 41:14.771
Now class, we're
going to pick up

41:14.771 --> 41:16.806
where we left off yesterday.

41:16.806 --> 41:17.740
If you'll please
take out your books

41:17.740 --> 41:19.876
and turn to page 375.

41:20.876 --> 41:23.947
(sighs loudly)

41:24.947 --> 41:27.050
- Hey, do you need some help?

41:27.050 --> 41:28.018
- That's okay, I'll
just go to the office.

41:29.018 --> 41:31.086
- [Michael] You don't have to
do that, I'll get it for you.

41:31.086 --> 41:32.023
(bangs loudly)

41:33.023 --> 41:33.023
There you go.

41:34.023 --> 41:35.057
- Thanks.

41:35.057 --> 41:36.192
- By the way, my name's Michael.

41:36.192 --> 41:37.693
- [Faith] Faith.

41:37.693 --> 41:39.061
- Yeah, I was just
in class with you.

41:39.061 --> 41:39.130
- Oh, yeah.

41:41.130 --> 41:42.699
- Don't worry about it.

41:42.699 --> 41:44.867
New school, you're
allowed to be nervous.

41:44.867 --> 41:46.268
- Come on, let's go.

41:46.268 --> 41:49.105
- Alright, well I gotta
go, see you around, Faith.

41:49.105 --> 41:52.601
(light dramatic music)

42:18.601 --> 42:20.369
- [Faith] Here, let me get that.

42:20.369 --> 42:22.007
- Ah, you are too kind.

42:25.007 --> 42:26.376
- It's no problem.

42:26.376 --> 42:27.943
Here, let me walk
you to your house.

42:27.943 --> 42:29.779
- You don't have to do that.

42:29.779 --> 42:30.880
- I want to.

42:31.880 --> 42:34.851
- You have such a giving heart.

42:34.851 --> 42:36.385
- Faith, what are you doing?

42:36.385 --> 42:40.028
- [Faith] It will just take a
second, I'll be right there.

42:46.028 --> 42:49.934
- You're such a
blessing to me, Faith.

42:51.934 --> 42:53.268
Do you know the Lord?

42:53.268 --> 42:54.005
- Yes, ma'am.

42:56.005 --> 43:00.213
- I believe he's got some
big plans for you, sweetie.

43:03.213 --> 43:07.018
Do you mind if I ask why
you're living next door?

43:08.018 --> 43:09.289
- It's a long story.

43:14.289 --> 43:17.293
Well, I need to get going.

43:17.293 --> 43:19.795
- Thank you so
much for your help.

43:19.795 --> 43:21.164
- I can pick up
your paper for you

43:21.164 --> 43:22.831
in the morning before
I head to school.

43:22.831 --> 43:24.400
- Oh, you don't have
to do that, sweetie.

43:24.400 --> 43:26.369
- No, I want to.

43:26.369 --> 43:28.103
- Well, thank you.

43:28.103 --> 43:29.405
- You're welcome.

43:29.405 --> 43:30.425
- Bu bye.
- Bye.

43:48.425 --> 43:51.784
(light piano music)

44:48.784 --> 44:52.289
♪ Somehow I started over again

44:54.289 --> 44:59.295
♪ Somehow I knew there'd
be no more chances

44:59.295 --> 45:03.132
♪ I've got to move
on and cut my losses

45:03.132 --> 45:06.034
♪ Letting go of heavy crosses

45:06.034 --> 45:09.072
♪ That bring me down to my knees

45:09.072 --> 45:11.273
♪ Til I have to say

45:11.273 --> 45:14.878
♪ I give up, take it all

45:14.878 --> 45:18.882
♪ I'm letting go and
trusting that you'll catch me

45:18.882 --> 45:23.418
♪ When I fall,
catch me when I fall

45:23.418 --> 45:27.257
♪ Open hands, broken heart

45:27.257 --> 45:29.559
♪ I'm leaving it to you to prove

45:29.559 --> 45:33.163
♪ A hope can come from heart

45:33.163 --> 45:37.311
♪ A hope can come from the heart

45:48.311 --> 45:52.317
♪ Somehow the morning
shatters the night

45:54.317 --> 45:58.954
♪ Somehow I know I'm so
close to being all right

45:58.954 --> 46:03.159
♪ I've trusted in way
too many shallow authors

46:03.159 --> 46:06.128
♪ Listened to so many scoffers

46:06.128 --> 46:09.231
♪ That poisoned my
mind and taken my soul

46:09.231 --> 46:11.266
♪ All this time, oh no

46:11.266 --> 46:14.938
♪ I give up, take it all

46:14.938 --> 46:17.373
♪ I'm letting go and trusting

46:17.373 --> 46:20.943
♪ that you'll catch
me when I fall

46:20.943 --> 46:23.246
♪ You'll catch me when I fall

46:23.246 --> 46:26.849
♪ Open hands, broken heart

46:26.849 --> 46:28.018
♪ I'm leaving it to you

46:29.018 --> 46:32.989
♪ To prove a hope
can come from heart

46:32.989 --> 46:35.025
♪ A hope can come

46:36.025 --> 46:38.293
♪ I'm loosening my grip

46:38.293 --> 46:42.297
