relationship with Jesus Christ?

56:52.942 --> 56:54.010
- Yes sir, they were
both Christians.

56:55.010 --> 56:56.512
- Well then, you have
the comfort in knowing

56:56.512 --> 56:57.913
that they were in
covenant with God

56:57.913 --> 56:59.215
through his son, Jesus Christ

56:59.215 --> 57:01.217
and they will have eternal life.

57:01.217 --> 57:05.521
- I know, I just
miss them so much.

57:05.521 --> 57:07.523
- It's okay to miss them

57:07.523 --> 57:08.990
and even a mourning
period is needed

57:08.990 --> 57:11.659
but when the time comes,
will you praise and thank God

57:11.659 --> 57:13.728
for the time you had
with your parents

57:13.728 --> 57:15.197
or will you be bitter?

57:15.197 --> 57:17.666
Always questioning
his reasoning?

57:17.666 --> 57:21.170
You see, the answers are
not always easy to find.

57:21.170 --> 57:25.240
Sometimes, we've got to
rely strictly on God's word.

57:25.240 --> 57:28.577
I'm sure you're familiar with
2 Corinthians Five and Seven.

57:28.577 --> 57:30.880
- For you walk by
faith, not by sight.

57:30.880 --> 57:34.182
- Keep the faith and
God'll see you through.

57:34.182 --> 57:35.751
- Thank you.

57:35.751 --> 57:37.152
- You're welcome, why
don't you come and join us

57:37.152 --> 57:40.025
for Sunday service,
we'd love to have you.

57:44.025 --> 57:46.663
(bell ringing)

57:47.663 --> 57:50.929
(light dramatic music)

58:20.929 --> 58:23.965
(phone ringing)

58:23.965 --> 58:25.601
- Hello?

58:25.601 --> 58:27.135
- [Michael] Hey, is this Faith?

58:27.135 --> 58:28.704
- Yes.

58:28.704 --> 58:30.306
- [Michael] This is
Michael from school.

58:30.306 --> 58:31.574
- Oh, hey.

58:32.574 --> 58:33.876
- [Michael] Listen, I
just wanted to apologize

58:33.876 --> 58:35.945
for walking in on
you the other day.

58:35.945 --> 58:37.246
I heard you from the hall

58:37.246 --> 58:38.014
and I don't know
what I was thinking.

58:39.014 --> 58:41.884
- It's fine, really,
don't worry about it.

58:41.884 --> 58:43.885
It's just, that was
the first time I sang

58:43.885 --> 58:46.922
in front of anybody
since my parents died.

58:46.922 --> 58:48.023
- [Michael] I'm
sorry, I had no idea.

58:49.023 --> 58:50.759
Can I make it up to you?

58:50.759 --> 58:53.128
Maybe I can take you
to dinner sometime?

58:53.128 --> 58:54.731
- Yeah, I'd like that.

58:56.731 --> 58:58.766
K, well I'll talk to you later.

58:58.766 --> 58:59.983
Bye.
- Bye.

59:14.983 --> 59:16.018
- Wow, you must be hungry.

59:17.018 --> 59:20.054
- Actually, I was hoping
I could bring this food

59:20.054 --> 59:21.023
to a girl I've seen in the park.

59:22.023 --> 59:23.224
She looks hungry.

59:23.224 --> 59:24.960
She looks like she needs help.

59:24.960 --> 59:29.297
- There's no stopping your
kindness is there, Faith?

59:29.297 --> 59:32.034
Just go ahead and
get what you need.

59:32.034 --> 59:33.378
- Thanks, Aunt Pam.

59:42.378 --> 59:43.679
Bye.
- Bye.

59:44.679 --> 59:47.163
(light dramatic music)

01:00:01.163 --> 01:00:04.094
Carol, you raised a
wonderful daughter.

01:01:40.094 --> 01:01:42.432
