are healthy throughout
the pregnancy.

01:09:45.511 --> 01:09:49.685
And I can tell you that every
child is a gift from God.

01:09:52.685 --> 01:09:54.693
Jade, wait, your medication.

01:09:58.693 --> 01:09:59.961
- Do you wanna go
get something to eat?

01:09:59.961 --> 01:10:02.396
- Sure.
- Alright, let's go.

01:10:02.396 --> 01:10:04.632
- Uh, you know, we played
baseball for a while, so...

01:10:04.632 --> 01:10:06.768
- Dear Lord, thank you
for your blessings.

01:10:06.768 --> 01:10:08.636
Thank you for the
food you provide.

01:10:08.636 --> 01:10:11.672
Please bless it to the
nourishment of our bodies, Amen.

01:10:11.672 --> 01:10:12.012
- Amen.

01:10:18.012 --> 01:10:20.748
So, I have a game on
Friday, are you gonna come?

01:10:20.748 --> 01:10:22.884
- Maybe.
- Maybe?

01:10:22.884 --> 01:10:24.590
Well, I hope you do.

01:10:28.590 --> 01:10:31.693
Have you decided on what you
wanna do with your music?

01:10:31.693 --> 01:10:34.962
- I don't know, I mean,
growing up I always thought

01:10:34.962 --> 01:10:37.931
I'd be doing something to
worship God with my music

01:10:37.931 --> 01:10:42.737
but now, after all that's
happened, I'm just not sure.

01:10:42.737 --> 01:10:45.573
I'm not entirely sure I
even wanna keep singing.

01:10:45.573 --> 01:10:47.708
- But Faith, you have
such an amazing gift.

01:10:47.708 --> 01:10:50.712
I don't think you realize how
your music affects people.

01:10:50.712 --> 01:10:54.849
- I love God but I'm just not
sure that people care anymore.

01:10:54.849 --> 01:10:57.618
So many have pulled away,

01:10:57.618 --> 01:11:00.387
all the awful things I've
seen these past few weeks.

01:11:00.387 --> 01:11:02.890
- But that's a reason why to
use your God-given talent.

01:11:02.890 --> 01:11:04.493
- I don't know.

01:11:06.493 --> 01:11:08.662
- I have an idea, why
don't you grab some friends

01:11:08.662 --> 01:11:10.765
and put a concert
on at the school?

01:11:10.765 --> 01:11:13.702
- A Jesus concert,
who would come?

01:11:13.702 --> 01:11:17.873
- I'll take care of that,
you just get ready to sing.

01:11:19.873 --> 01:11:22.747
(chattering)

01:11:25.747 --> 01:11:27.881
(light dramatic music)

01:11:27.881 --> 01:11:30.576
(phone ringing)

01:12:28.576 --> 01:12:30.945
- God, it's been a while.

01:12:31.945 --> 01:12:33.682
I hardly know what to say.

01:12:35.682 --> 01:12:36.623
I need your help.

01:12:42.623 --> 01:12:45.096
God, I'm sorry for
all that I've done.

01:12:49.096 --> 01:12:51.170
I tried to do everything right.

01:12:55.170 --> 01:12:57.806
Look what it's got me.

01:12:58.806 --> 01:13:00.679
I lost my wife, my daughter,

01:13:04.679 --> 01:13:06.954
and now I'm here all alone.

01:13:13.954 --> 01:13:15.064
All I have is my job.

01:13:24.064 --> 01:13:25.234
Please help me, God.

01:13:27.234 --> 01:13:30.984
Please help me find
my daughter, please.

01:13:43.984 --> 01:13:47.729
(light dramatic music)

01:13:54.729 --> 01:13:56.831
- Roger, I thought you
were coming home hours ago.

01:13:56.831 --> 01:13:57.966
- Chill out, I'll be home later.

01:13:57.966 --> 01:13:59.667
- No, you're coming home now.

01:13:59.667 --> 01:14:01.970
- I said I'll be home
later, don't piss me off.

01:14:01.970 --> 01:14:03.805
- I'm not living
like this anymore.

01:14:03.805 --> 01:14:06.507
It's either this or it's us

01:14:06.507 --> 01:14:09.744
and I'm praying you choose us.

01:14:10.744 --> 01:14:12.823
I'm going home.

01:14:21.823 --> 01:14:23.056
- You're doing what?

01:14:23.056 --> 01:14:25.560
- Putting on a
concert at school.

01:14:25.560 --> 01:14:26.860
- Who put you up to that?

01:14:26.860 --> 01:14:28.896
- Oh, some guy.

01:14:28.896 --> 01:14:30.599
- Oh, a boyfriend?

01:14:31.599 --> 01:14:33.701
- No, not a boyfriend.

01:14:33.701 --> 01:14:35.168
- Sounds like you're doing
pretty well for yourself,

01:14:35.168 --> 01:14:37.838
new school, new boyfriend.

01:14:37.838 --> 01:14:40.041
- Anyways, we're
planning this concert

01:14:40.041 --> 01:14:42.944
and I was wondering,
do you guys want in?

01:14:42.944 --> 01:14:43.978
- I'm in.

01:14:43.978 --> 01:14:46.180
- Faith, you know I'll be there.

01:14:46.180 --> 01:14:48.783
- I'll be there too, Faith.

01:14:48.783 --> 01:14:49.751
- Have you been
there the whole time?

01:14:49.751 --> 01:14:51.085
- Hush, Nevaeh.

01:14:51.085 --> 01:14:53.587
Now Faith, what's this
boyfriend I hear about?

01:14:53.587 --> 01:14:54.956
- Give it back.

01:14:54.956 --> 01:14:57.292
- [Girl] Does he have
a little brother?

01:14:57.292 --> 01:15:00.005
(light dramatic music)

01:15:11.005 --> 01:15:13.944
- God, please help me.

01:15:16.944 --> 01:15:20.685
I have nowhere to go
and no one wants me.

01:15:23.685 --> 01:15:25.092
(crying)

01:15:32.092 --> 01:15:35.945
(light dramatic music)

01:15:51.945 --> 01:15:53.083
- I'm home.

01:15:56.083 --> 01:15:58.219
- Roger, what are you doing?

01:15:58.219 --> 01:15:59.686
You told me to come home.

01:15:59.686 --> 01:16:02.189
- That was hours
ago, you're drunk.

01:16:02.189 --> 01:16:04.826
- Ah, here comes the priest.

01:16:04.826 --> 01:16:07.694
You here to tell me
I'm going to hell?

01:16:07.694 --> 01:16:09.130
- Roger, that's enough.

01:16:09.130 --> 01:16:11.164
- I say when it's enough.

01:16:11.164 --> 01:16:12.766
You know, there is no God.

01:16:12.766 --> 01:16:14.101
You know how I know?

01:16:14.101 --> 01:16:18.038
Because I got you instead
of my own baby girl

01:16:18.038 --> 01:16:20.140
and if there is
a God, he's cruel

01:16:20.140 --> 01:16:22.710
because now you're here,
living in my house,

01:16:22.710 --> 01:16:25.078
eating my food, trying
to change my life.

01:16:25.078 --> 01:16:27.114
- I didn't try to
change anything.

01:16:27.114 --> 01:16:28.850
- Take my wife to church,

01:16:28.850 --> 01:16:30.885
messing with the
old bag next door.

01:16:30.885 --> 01:16:32.386
- I was just trying to help.

01:16:32.386 --> 01:16:35.791
- Stop trying,
you're not helping.

01:16:36.791 --> 01:16:38.760
Every day that I
have to see your face

01:16:38.760 --> 01:16:42.130
reminds me of the
daughter I lost.

01:16:42.130 --> 01:16:43.032
That's how I know
there's no God.

01:16:44.032 --> 01:16:45.298
- I don't know what
you want from me.

01:16:45.298 --> 01:16:46.333
- Get out of my house!

01:16:46.333 --> 01:16:47.046
- Roger!
- Go!

01:16:58.046 --> 01:17:01.248
(light dramatic music)

01:17:35.248 --> 01:17:37.297
(crying)

01:17:50.297 --> 01:17:51.800
- Wait!

01:17:52.800 --> 01:17:55.235
Listen, I don't know what
you've been going through

01:17:55.235 --> 01:17:57.805
but this isn't the answer.

01:17:57.805 --> 01:17:59.239
- You don't know me.

01:17:59.239 --> 01:18:03.945
- I've seen you around, I've
been wanting to help you

01:18:04.945 --> 01:18:08.783
and my Mom used to
tell me before she died

01:18:08.783 --> 01:18:11.284
that one small
gesture or kind word

01:18:11.284 --> 01:18:14.087
can change someone's life.

01:18:14.087 --> 01:18:16.289
I know you may
feel lost right now

01:18:16.289 --> 01:18:19.063
but there's a God
and he loves you.

01:18:22.063 --> 01:18:24.532
He's the one that
directed me to help you.

01:18:24.532 --> 01:18:26.434
It's because of his love for you

01:18:26.434 --> 01:18:28.202
that led me here tonight.

01:18:28.202 --> 01:18:29.503
- You really believe that?

01:18:29.503 --> 01:18:30.105
- Yes, I do.

01:18:32.105 --> 01:18:35.376
And even though we don't
understand it sometimes,

01:18:35.376 --> 01:18:38.279
God is at work in
our lives every day

01:18:38.279 --> 01:18:42.048
to sow his plan
that he has for us.

01:18:42.048 --> 01:18:44.318
You must be hungry.

01:18:44.318 --> 01:18:48.555
How about we grab something
to eat and talk, my treat.

01:18:48.555 --> 01:18:49.126
- Sure.

01:18:52.126 --> 01:18:55.115
(uplifting rock music)

01:19:15.115 --> 01:19:18.854
♪ The flood of your spirit

01:19:19.854 --> 01:19:24.559
♪ Rushes me deeper
than waters wild

01:19:24.559 --> 01:19:27.596
♪ Come by the river

01:19:29.596 --> 01:19:33.975
♪ Showers of mercy that
wash over me, over me

01:19:40.975 --> 01:19:45.179
♪ All that I long for
and all that I need

01:19:45.179 --> 01:19:48.551
♪ Is hands of glory

01:19:50.551 --> 01:19:55.355
♪ All that I hope for,
all my heart desires, Lord

01:19:55.355 --> 01:19:58.360
♪ Is just one moment

01:20:00.360 --> 01:20:03.564
♪ A glimpse of glory

01:20:03.564 --> 01:20:06.634
(phone ringing)

01:20:06.634 --> 01:20:07.403
- Hello?

01:20:09.403 --> 01:20:10.537
- [Jade] Hey, Dad.

01:20:10.537 --> 01:20:13.573
- Jade, where are you?

01:20:13.573 --> 01:20:16.476
I've been looking
all over for you.

01:20:16.476 --> 01:20:19.248
- You've been looking for me?

01:20:21.248 --> 01:20:25.485
- I haven't been a real
good father to you.

01:20:25.485 --> 01:20:31.359
When your mother left, that's
when you needed me most

01:20:31.359 --> 01:20:33.895
and I wasn't there for you.

01:20:33.895 --> 01:20:36.030
I'm sorry, Jade, I love you.

01:20:37.030 --> 01:20:38.301
- You still love me?

01:20:40.301 --> 01:20:43.304
- Baby girl, I love you,
it's just you and me

01:20:43.304 --> 01:20:44.006
and we're gonna get
through this together.

01:20:45.006 --> 01:20:46.539
♪ All that I hope for,
all my heart desires,

01:20:46.539 --> 01:20:50.412
♪ Lord, is just one moment

01:20:52.412 --> 01:20:55.355
♪ A glimpse of glory

01:21:02.355 --> 01:21:03.630
- Bye.
- Bye.

01:21:09.630 --> 01:21:14.402
- I shouldn't have
let you go like that.

01:21:14.402 --> 01:21:15.570
- Wait.

01:21:17.570 --> 01:21:19.573
Here's your Bible back.

01:21:19.573 --> 01:21:21.509
- No, I want you to have it.

01:21:21.509 --> 01:21:23.144
- Thank you.

01:21:23.144 --> 01:21:25.645
♪ All that I long for
and all that I need

01:21:25.645 --> 01:21:29.953
♪ Is a glimpse of glory

01:21:31.953 --> 01:21:35.957
♪ All that I hope for,
all my heart desires

01:21:35.957 --> 01:21:40.567
♪ Lord, is just one
moment, a glimpse of glory

01:21:46.567 --> 01:21:49.039
♪ All that I long for

01:21:53.039 --> 01:21:56.377
♪ And all that I need

01:21:56.377 --> 01:22:00.649
♪ And all that I long for

01:22:02.649 --> 01:22:05.387
♪ Glimpse of glory

01:22:07.387 --> 01:22:10.393
♪ Glimpse of glory

01:22:12.393 --> 01:22:15.430
♪ Glimpse of glory

01:22:17.430 --> 01:22:20.737
♪ Glimpse of glory

01:22:22.737 --> 01:22:24.573
- Thank you, God.

01:22:25.573 --> 01:22:27.442
Thank you for Jade.

01:22:28.442 --> 01:22:30.644
If it means saving her life,

01:22:30.644 --> 01:22:34.515
coming to this
city was worth it.

01:22:34.515 --> 01:22:37.118
And thank you for my friends,

01:22:37.118 --> 01:22:41.490
Samantha and Nevaeh, they're
always there when I need them,

01:22:43.490 --> 01:22:46.426
even if they're hours away.

01:22:46.426 --> 01:22:49.631
And Michael, thank you for him.

01:22:51.631 --> 01:22:56.670
He's given me hope
that I thought I lost.

01:22:56.670 --> 01:22:59.376
And lastly, thank
you for my parents.

01:23:02.376 --> 01:23:07.547
Thank you for the time I
got to spend with them.

01:23:07.547 --> 01:23:10.350
Thank you for the lessons
I learned from them

01:23:10.350 --> 01:23:13.823
that help me, even
now that they're gone.

01:23:15.823 --> 01:23:17.524
Thank you for
helping me understand

01:23:17.524 --> 01:23:20.529
that they're always with me.

01:23:21.529 --> 01:23:24.431
Tell them I love them.

01:23:24.431 --> 01:23:26.335
Just tell them for me.

01:23:28.335 --> 01:23:31.439
Thank you for never
leaving me, God.

01:23:31.439 --> 01:23:32.810
Thank you.

01:23:36.810 --> 01:23:39.595
(phone vibrating)

01:23:54.595 --> 01:23:56.296
- I'm sorry I took
so long to get you.

01:23:56.296 --> 01:23:59.733
Roger, I was trying
to calm him down.

01:23:59.733 --> 01:24:01.268
- How is he?

01:24:01.268 --> 01:24:04.604
- He's passed out on the couch.

01:24:04.604 --> 01:24:07.376
He will feel it
tomorrow, though.

01:24:09.376 --> 01:24:11.145
- What was he talking about?

01:24:11.145 --> 01:24:13.315
He said he lost his baby girl.

01:24:15.315 --> 01:24:18.551
- Your mother had a hard time
getting pregnant with you.

01:24:18.551 --> 01:24:20.354
- I've heard that.

01:24:20.354 --> 01:24:21.490
- I had problems, too.

01:24:23.490 --> 01:24:28.162
And finally, after what
seemed like forever of trying,

01:24:28.162 --> 01:24:33.701
I got pregnant and two weeks
later, Carol got pregnant, too.

01:24:33.701 --> 01:24:35.804
- I didn't know that.

01:24:36.804 --> 01:24:38.805
- Me and your mother thought
it was the best thing

01:24:38.805 --> 01:24:40.444
that could ever happen.

01:24:43.444 --> 01:24:45.746
For the kids to grow
up and be best friends,

01:24:45.746 --> 01:24:50.520
just like we were but our
little daughter didn't make it.

01:24:53.520 --> 01:24:57.158
(light dramatic music)

01:24:57.158 --> 01:24:58.561
- I'm so sorry.

01:25:01.561 --> 01:25:03.663
- It's not your fault

01:25:03.663 --> 01:25:07.636
and as much as Roger
says it is, it's not.

01:25:09.636 --> 01:25:12.407
It's just hard to look at you

01:25:13.407 --> 01:25:16.578
and think of what
could have been.

01:25:18.578 --> 01:25:22.515
That's why Roger is
the man he is today

01:25:22.515 --> 01:25:24.485
and the woman I am.

01:25:25.485 --> 01:25:28.322
We never let it go
and we blamed God

01:25:28.322 --> 01:25:30.725
for the loss of our daughter.

01:25:32.725 --> 01:25:35.530
I wasn't sure
about you moving in

01:25:37.530 --> 01:25:40.234
but when I saw you
help our neighbor

01:25:40.234 --> 01:25:43.673
and you took food to
the girl in the park,

01:25:46.673 --> 01:25:50.648
you didn't stop living but
we did, we stopped living.

01:25:54.648 --> 01:25:57.752
- It's not too late, Aunt Pam.

01:25:58.752 --> 01:26:01.654
- I can't apologize to Carol.

01:26:01.654 --> 01:26:04.960
And Roger, he's so far gone.

01:26:05.960 --> 01:26:08.796
I don't think I'll
ever get him back.

01:26:08.796 --> 01:26:11.698
- You have to have faith.

01:26:11.698 --> 01:26:14.680
- I have Faith,
she's right here.

01:26:27.680 --> 01:26:29.802
(groaning)

01:26:49.802 --> 01:26:53.831
(light dramatic music)

01:27:17.831 --> 01:27:18.408
- Pam?

01:27:27.408 --> 01:27:28.716
Pam?

01:27:35.716 --> 01:27:36.966
Faith?

01:27:52.966 --> 01:27:54.702
- Hey Caleb, what are
you doing this weeekend?

01:27:54.702 --> 01:27:56.569
- I don't know, me and the
boys might go to the mall.

01:27:56.569 --> 01:27:57.970
- That sounds fun,
you wanna go, too?

01:27:57.970 --> 01:27:59.472
- Yeah, we should totally go.
- I think we should.

01:27:59.472 --> 01:28:01.444
- I might hit y'all up.

01:28:03.444 --> 01:28:04.877
But I'll catch you all later.

01:28:04.877 --> 01:28:06.372
- Alright.
- Bye.

01:28:31.372 --> 01:28:32.672
- Oh, I'm sorry.

01:28:32.672 --> 01:28:37.543
- Wait, I heard you
sing in the music hall.

01:28:37.543 --> 01:28:38.947
It was fantastic.

01:28:39.947 --> 01:28:40.881
- You were the one
that sang at church

01:28:40.881 --> 01:28:42.916
the other week, right?

01:28:42.916 --> 01:28:44.417
You did really good.

01:28:44.417 --> 01:28:45.819
- Yeah, you should join
the music club here.

01:28:45.819 --> 01:28:47.854
We could really use your talent.

01:28:47.854 --> 01:28:48.689
- Really?

01:28:48.689 --> 01:28:49.759
- Yeah.

01:28:51.759 --> 01:28:54.028
(light dramatic music)

01:29:28.028 --> 01:29:30.644
(soft piano music)

01:29:43.644 --> 01:29:46.880
- I don't know what
I'm doing here.

01:29:46.880 --> 01:29:49.822
I don't even know what to do.

01:29:54.822 --> 01:29:55.225
- Roger?

01:29:58.225 --> 01:29:59.594
Is that you?

01:30:00.594 --> 01:30:02.064
- Ah, I was just leaving.

01:30:04.064 --> 01:30:08.237
- Well if you came in here,
there must be a reason.

01:30:10.237 --> 01:30:15.208
- [Roger] I don't know
what I'm doing here.

01:30:15.208 --> 01:30:17.948
- Some people come for guidance.

01:30:21.948 --> 01:30:26.220
Roger, I've lived next
door to you for years

01:30:26.220 --> 01:30:30.490
and I've never seen you
come in here before.

01:30:30.490 --> 01:30:31.560
You seem so upset.

01:30:33.560 --> 01:30:35.130
Do you wanna talk about it?

01:30:37.130 --> 01:30:39.667
- I think I lost my wife.

01:30:41.667 --> 01:30:43.939
I messed up bad.

01:30:45.939 --> 01:30:48.944
- And you want forgiveness.

01:30:50.944 --> 01:30:52.012
- It's too late for that.

01:30:53.012 --> 01:30:56.550
- It's never too late
for forgiveness, Roger.

01:30:56.550 --> 01:31:00.023
That's what the love and the
grace of God is all about.

01:31:03.023 --> 01:31:05.958
- I don't even know
if I believe in God.

01:31:05.958 --> 01:31:10.264
- So, you came in here,
set down in this pew,

01:31:10.264 --> 01:31:15.068
in this sanctuary,
trying to convince me

01:31:15.068 --> 01:31:17.309
to convince you otherwise?

01:31:22.309 --> 01:31:25.018
No, Roger, God is
all about forgiveness

01:31:31.018 --> 01:31:34.555
and I think that's
why you came in here.

01:31:34.555 --> 01:31:37.761
This is the perfect
place to find it.

01:31:40.761 --> 01:31:42.762
(breathing heavily)

01:31:42.762 --> 01:31:45.712
May I pray for you
and your family?

01:31:59.712 --> 01:32:02.850
- I'm so sorry, I can change.

01:32:04.850 --> 01:32:07.025
I promise you, I will change.

01:32:13.025 --> 01:32:14.360
(students chattering)

01:32:14.360 --> 01:32:19.099
- Hey, you should
come to the concert.

01:32:19.099 --> 01:32:22.668
Y'all should come
to the concert.

01:32:22.668 --> 01:32:25.939
- Oh no, we are
not going to this.

01:32:25.939 --> 01:32:26.907
- What are you doing
this weekend, Michael?

01:32:26.907 --> 01:32:28.240
- I don't know--

01:32:28.240 --> 01:32:31.890
- Hey, you should come
to the concert, you too.

01:32:44.890 --> 01:32:46.960
- [Girl] This place is huge.

01:32:46.960 --> 01:32:48.029
